Dialogue: 2,0:01:25.02,0:01:31.02,mushisign,,0,0,0,,{\fad(2000,0)\blur0.6\pos(310,95)}The Shadow that Devours the Sun
Dialogue: 5,0:01:35.32,0:01:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Doctor Adashino.
Dialogue: 5,0:01:37.20,0:01:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatcha looking at?
Dialogue: 5,0:01:38.52,0:01:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 5,0:01:39.94,0:01:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, there's gonna be a solar eclipse one month from today.
Dialogue: 5,0:01:43.32,0:01:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What's a solar eclipse?
Dialogue: 5,0:01:44.97,0:01:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's when the sun hides behind the moon.
Dialogue: 5,0:01:47.84,0:01:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{Really?}
Dialogue: 5,0:01:48.94,0:01:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it gonna be any fun?
Dialogue: 5,0:01:50.54,0:01:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 5,0:01:52.19,0:01:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's gonna get dark around here for a while,
Dialogue: 5,0:01:55.28,0:01:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and according to my mushi-shi buddy,
Dialogue: 5,0:01:57.30,0:01:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the mushi should become really active.
Dialogue: 5,0:02:00.03,0:02:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So even those who can't normally see them may get a chance to{ see them}.
Dialogue: 5,0:02:05.30,0:02:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I'm kinda looking forward to it.
Dialogue: 5,0:02:07.44,0:02:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{Huh...}
Dialogue: 5,0:02:08.68,0:02:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You never change, Doctor.
Dialogue: 5,0:02:10.72,0:02:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Be quiet.{He's telling them to butt out of his behavior.}{}
Dialogue: 5,0:02:12.16,0:02:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Will that mushi-shi come by again?
Dialogue: 5,0:02:14.44,0:02:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I sent a letter inviting him, but he responded \Nsaying he's gotta take care of something first.{The tenses here are incorrect, but the doctor's one of the few adults I have speak informally.}
Dialogue: 5,0:02:18.95,0:02:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{Huh.}
Dialogue: 5,0:02:20.08,0:02:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe he's busy 'cause \Nthe mushi are gonna act up.
Dialogue: 5,0:02:22.97,0:02:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe.
Dialogue: 5,0:02:25.31,0:02:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows what he's up to?
Dialogue: 5,0:02:56.73,0:02:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Tanyuu.
Dialogue: 5,0:02:59.85,0:03:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 5,0:03:01.89,0:03:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the last of the \Nrecords we have on eclipses.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:09.34,0:03:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:14.27,0:03:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}These are records of the behavioral changes \Nsaid to occur in mushi when the sun is eclipsed
Dialogue: 5,0:03:19.46,0:03:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}as well as how to deal with those changes.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:23.25,0:03:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Many mushi favor the altered light and gain strength from it,
Dialogue: 5,0:03:28.12,0:03:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}which thereby increases the number of \Npeople under their influence.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:32.99,0:03:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}These {numerous remaining}records mention the following incidents.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:35.71,0:03:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}One: the formation of a pillar of mushi.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:39.64,0:03:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Mushi may gather to form a column.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:42.60,0:03:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}One must not linger near the pillar lest {gender-neutral }they fall under its influence.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:49.01,0:03:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The pillar should disperse \Nnot long after the eclipse passes.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:53.75,0:03:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Should it not disperse,
Dialogue: 5,0:03:55.44,0:03:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the mushi-sending ceremony should be performed.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:59.89,0:04:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Two: people with a fear of sunlight.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:03.71,0:04:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Following the eclipse,
Dialogue: 5,0:04:05.22,0:04:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}there may be those who fear sunlight and no longer behave normally.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:10.09,0:04:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This is due to being possessed by \NYain, or "Night Shadow" mushi{, during the eclipse}.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:14.71,0:04:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Curing them will require three tenths more than the normal amount of the mushi-purging drug.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:20.77,0:04:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Three: those who cannot sleep.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:23.81,0:04:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Some people may have damaged their eyes from \Nexcessive exposure to the sun during the eclipse.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:29.28,0:04:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Their condition may persist even after sundown,
Dialogue: 5,0:04:32.50,0:04:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and they may be unable to sleep.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:35.59,0:04:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This anomaly is caused by \NShirayami, or "White Darkness" mushi.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:38.39,0:04:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The afflicted can be cured by continued exposure to {light from }the River of Light or to light emanated by mushi.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:46.07,0:04:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Four: people who vanish.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:49.21,0:04:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There may be those who \Nbecome invisible after the eclipse.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:52.88,0:04:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This condition is limited to those who \Npossess the innate ability to see mushi.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:56.79,0:05:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Those under the mushi's influence often wander into the mountains
Dialogue: 5,0:05:00.24,0:05:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and may reappear atop an elevated place.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:04.67,0:05:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It is also common for the afflicted to remain invisible forever.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:08.57,0:05:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\q2}If they manage to retain their form, the only cure is \Nto bring them back and treat them with great compassion.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:14.59,0:05:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}However, many end up wandering \Nback to the mountains, never to return.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:22.51,0:05:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you discover something?
Dialogue: 5,0:05:24.24,0:05:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Most of the incidents in our records \Nwere caused by well-known{ to mushi-shi} mushi,
Dialogue: 5,0:05:30.10,0:05:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,so this eclipse shouldn't cause much confusion.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:33.67,0:05:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,However, there is one \Nphenomenon that concerns me.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:37.57,0:05:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,If it should come to pass,
Dialogue: 5,0:05:39.50,0:05:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,it will prove troublesome if we \Ndo not make appropriate preparations.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:42.52,0:05:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:43.53,0:05:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But as these are the only records that remain,
