Dialogue: 5,0:05:48.53,0:05:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,it will be difficult to predict \Nwhere the phenomenon may occur.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:57.89,0:05:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's finally time.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:01.77,0:06:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope I'll be able to see it despite the clouds.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:06.73,0:06:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,In any case, that Ginko...
Dialogue: 5,0:06:08.97,0:06:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I ask him to teach me how to \Ncapture mushi during the eclipse,
Dialogue: 5,0:06:11.68,0:06:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and instead, he just sends me these packets of medicine.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:14.32,0:06:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor!
Dialogue: 5,0:06:15.56,0:06:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We told everyone that there'd be an eclipse soon and not to panic.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:20.56,0:06:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We also told them not to look at it for \Ntoo long, 'cause it could hurt their eyes.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:24.44,0:06:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:25.24,0:06:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Good job.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:26.82,0:06:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You kids better not look{ at it} either.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:28.35,0:06:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!{lol}
Dialogue: 5,0:06:29.44,0:06:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But we really wanna{ at least just a little}!
Dialogue: 5,0:06:30.88,0:06:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 5,0:06:31.70,0:06:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, I have {\i1}these{\i0}, so I can look all I want.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:34.04,0:06:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 5,0:06:34.70,0:06:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not fair! \NHow come {\i1}you{\i0} get to?
Dialogue: 5,0:06:36.16,0:06:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Lemme see 'em!
Dialogue: 5,0:06:37.32,0:06:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,C'mon! Give it to us!
Dialogue: 5,0:06:38.14,0:06:39.71,Alt,,0,0,0,,Hey, don't break it{, idiot}!
Dialogue: 5,0:06:43.21,0:06:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Tanyuu.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:45.69,0:06:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You should seek shelter in the cellar soon.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:48.22,0:06:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to protect yourself from the light.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:51.71,0:06:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I should be all right.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:53.43,0:06:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to see it for myself{,} at least once.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:57.89,0:07:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Your health is of the utmost importance.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:02.07,0:07:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:10.21,0:07:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope everyone will be okay.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:31.93,0:07:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like it's starting.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:34.88,0:07:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{Oh, }Look! The sun!
Dialogue: 5,0:07:40.64,0:07:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's missing a piece!
Dialogue: 5,0:07:42.00,0:07:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa, it really is!
Dialogue: 5,0:07:44.08,0:07:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to the clouds, you can see it with the naked eye.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:50.93,0:07:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,This is so frightening.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:54.04,0:07:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about? \NSomething just like this happened when I was a boy.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:58.45,0:08:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything will be back to \Nnormal before you know it.{still talking in past tense, but this is acceptable}
Dialogue: 5,0:08:05.05,0:08:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so cold.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:14.45,0:08:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,What are these?
Dialogue: 5,0:08:16.37,0:08:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are they?!
Dialogue: 5,0:08:17.58,0:08:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,There. And there too.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:19.81,0:08:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 5,0:08:21.36,0:08:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I still can't see 'em!
Dialogue: 5,0:09:31.52,0:09:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The sun's completely gone.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:34.67,0:09:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Nah, it's only hidden.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:36.52,0:09:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The sun will be out again in no time.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:39.03,0:09:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But you kids should remember this fear.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:43.13,0:09:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, without the sun,
Dialogue: 5,0:09:45.06,0:09:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,none of us can continue living.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:50.91,0:09:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Here it comes.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:59.03,0:10:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow! It's so warm!
Dialogue: 5,0:10:01.74,0:10:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank goodness!
Dialogue: 5,0:10:10.09,0:10:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that was a surprise.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:12.56,0:10:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It certainly was.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:15.03,0:10:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? What's that?
Dialogue: 5,0:10:18.46,0:10:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So it came?
Dialogue: 5,0:10:24.18,0:10:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What in the world is going on?
Dialogue: 5,0:10:26.52,0:10:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never seen anything like this before.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:29.39,0:10:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The sun's disappearing again.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:32.29,0:10:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Strange things are gathering near it, too.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:35.48,0:10:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? What strange things?
Dialogue: 5,0:10:37.19,0:10:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Those{\i0} strange things! They're floating up{ in the sky} \Nand making that shadow bigger and bigger.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:43.07,0:10:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He's right.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:44.40,0:10:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? I don't see anything.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:47.74,0:10:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, everyone, remain calm.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:50.26,0:10:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Just the other day, this man here—
Dialogue: 5,0:10:52.80,0:10:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What was your name, again?
Dialogue: 5,0:10:55.21,0:10:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I am Ginko, a mushi-shi.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:57.85,0:11:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday, he came to me
Dialogue: 5,0:11:00.68,0:11:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and told me that strange things \Nmay occur here during the eclipse.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:04.95,0:11:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, what he said has come to pass.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:08.80,0:11:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, {he said }he needs all of your help to set this right.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:14.33,0:11:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,At the center of the shadow obscuring \Nthe sun is a Hihami, or "Sun Devourer" mushi.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:19.50,0:11:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It is calling smaller mushi to it and causing them to multiply, thus expanding the shadow.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:25.67,0:11:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Although a Hihami typically \Nremains hidden deep underground,
Dialogue: 5,0:11:28.38,0:11:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,during an eclipse, it separates into a "core" and a "root,"
Dialogue: 5,0:11:31.46,0:11:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and its core ascends into the sky.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:34.87,0:11:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It is said that in order to vanquish it,
Dialogue: 5,0:11:36.36,0:11:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,we must search the nearby grounds, find the Hihami's root,
Dialogue: 5,0:11:39.74,0:11:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and expose it to the sun.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:42.59,0:11:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 5,0:11:43.84,0:11:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the exact location of the root is unknown.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:47.99,0:11:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,All we can do is dig in areas \Nthat feel different from usual.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:55.39,0:11:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,How are we supposed to find \Nanything with a description like that?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:58.48,0:12:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Have {\i1}you{\i0} seen anything unusual?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:00.70,0:12:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:02.08,0:12:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you help him, everyone?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:04.36,0:12:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't just stand idly by.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:06.28,0:12:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,How about splitting up and searching?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:17.21,0:12:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:19.57,0:12:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Nah, nothing out of the ordinary.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:22.03,0:12:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing here either!
Dialogue: 5,0:12:24.35,0:12:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:25.44,0:12:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, please continue searching.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:31.87,0:12:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We searched all day and didn't find a thing.{TLC Too much of a stretch?}
Dialogue: 5,0:12:34.44,0:12:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:35.85,0:12:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, maybe come tomorrow, \Nthe sun will be back out like nothing happened.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:41.95,0:12:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, maybe.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:54.05,0:12:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Must be from Tanyuu.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:56.93,0:12:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The eclipse ended without incident here.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:00.19,0:13:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The mushi-shi that {"who" is correct here, according to prescriptivist grammarians, but I thought "that" sounded a little less confusing.}I sent to the areas \Nin which I suspected a Hihami might appear
Dialogue: 5,0:13:04.34,0:13:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}have all reported that nothing was out of the ordinary in those areas.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:08.51,0:13:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}How are things on your end?
Dialogue: 5,0:13:12.47,0:13:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You were right on the money.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:20.49,0:13:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though it's morning, it's still so dark.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:23.12,0:13:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a little depressing.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:27.53,0:13:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you find anything over there?
Dialogue: 5,0:13:30.74,0:13:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Nope, nothing.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:33.79,0:13:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Does this "root" even exist?
Dialogue: 5,0:13:51.59,0:13:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,How many days has it been already?
Dialogue: 5,0:13:53.42,0:13:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We haven't found a damn thing.{anything even remotely unusual}
Dialogue: 5,0:13:55.94,0:13:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I've had enough of this too.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:58.15,0:13:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you!
Dialogue: 5,0:13:59.48,0:14:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell us in detail what this \Nroot of yours looks like!{lewd}{lel}
Dialogue: 5,0:14:02.57,0:14:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Its location and appearance vary \Neach time it is mentioned in the records.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:06.40,0:14:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I know this must be unsettling,
Dialogue: 5,0:14:08.46,0:14:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,but please remain calm{,} and continue searching.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:10.64,0:14:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you possibly expect us to believe you?
Dialogue: 5,0:14:15.13,0:14:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We're done for.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:17.45,0:14:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Without the sun, all our \Nrice paddies and fields will dry up.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:22.69,0:14:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Unless we manage to stock up on food now,
Dialogue: 5,0:14:24.82,0:14:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,none of us will survive the winter.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:30.05,0:14:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}After losing something \Ncentral to their daily lives,{Using a comma here instead of an em dash.}
Dialogue: 5,0:14:33.43,0:14:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}after losing something \Nthey never thought they would{ lose},
Dialogue: 5,0:14:40.11,0:14:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}what do people draw on for strength?
Dialogue: 5,0:14:43.57,0:14:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And in place of that original something,
Dialogue: 5,0:14:47.20,0:14:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}what do they base their life around{ in its stead}?
Dialogue: 5,0:14:58.89,0:15:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The shutters are closed, \Neven in this darkness?
Dialogue: 5,0:15:01.59,0:15:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The place doesn't seem abandoned, though.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:09.93,0:15:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}White hair, pale skin, and pale eyes.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:13.87,0:15:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This must be...
Dialogue: 5,0:15:19.48,0:15:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiyori! What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 5,0:15:21.40,0:15:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's still day!
Dialogue: 5,0:15:22.85,0:15:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But the sun's completely gone.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:25.82,0:15:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Now even {\i1}I{\i0} can go outside.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:28.44,0:15:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But, Hiyori!
Dialogue: 5,0:15:33.35,0:15:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 5,0:15:36.01,0:15:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Your hair...
Dialogue: 5,0:15:37.34,0:15:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have the same sickness as me?
Dialogue: 5,0:15:40.07,0:15:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,No clue.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:41.32,0:15:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know why I look the way I do,
Dialogue: 5,0:15:44.26,0:15:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,but I'm fine in the sunlight.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:46.93,0:15:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:48.55,0:15:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiyori, are you sure you're okay outside?{>hiyori. such a cruel name}
Dialogue: 5,0:15:53.10,0:15:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm fine.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:54.40,0:15:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 5,0:15:55.21,0:15:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing's happening!
Dialogue: 5,0:15:57.29,0:15:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I know!
Dialogue: 5,0:15:58.36,0:15:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Hinata.{>hinata. gdi}
Dialogue: 5,0:15:59.50,0:16:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go see that \Nmeadow you told me about{ when we were younger}.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:02.39,0:16:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:03.42,0:16:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything in our fields died, \Nso I have to go into town and sell something.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:08.25,0:16:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiyori!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:09.23,0:16:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:10.66,0:16:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Your marks are gonna come back!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:12.28,0:16:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Get back inside.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:14.99,0:16:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Do these "marks" look like black spots?
Dialogue: 5,0:16:20.37,0:16:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You're that mushi-shi the elder introduced to us.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:24.17,0:16:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What's it to you?
Dialogue: 5,0:16:26.33,0:16:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I've heard that the subspecies of mushi {that is }responsible for this eclipse can also cause symptoms like hers.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:32.91,0:16:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you cure her?
Dialogue: 5,0:16:36.03,0:16:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, a treatment has yet to be found.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:40.56,0:16:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think you could tell me more?
Dialogue: 5,0:16:48.97,0:16:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I just remembered something from what you said earlier.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:52.65,0:16:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Back when my wife had just become pregnant with our daughters,
Dialogue: 5,0:16:55.72,0:16:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,we saw something similar to the eclipse today...
Dialogue: 5,0:17:00.51,0:17:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,except that time, it was the moon.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:04.75,0:17:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at the moon, dear.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:07.91,0:17:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,As with this eclipse, the moon \Ndisappeared right before our eyes.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:12.30,0:17:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember finding it strangely ominous.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:17.39,0:17:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, what's wrong?
Dialogue: 5,0:17:18.92,0:17:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 5,0:17:21.19,0:17:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm okay. I'm not sure \Nwhat just happened{, though}.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:23.80,0:17:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt faint all of a sudden.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:27.79,0:17:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,My wife safely gave birth to our twin daughters,
Dialogue: 5,0:17:30.82,0:17:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,but one of them was born with \Nwhite hair, pale skin, and pale eyes.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:37.73,0:17:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,My wife never recovered after giving birth to them,
Dialogue: 5,0:17:40.84,0:17:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and she soon passed away.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:49.33,0:17:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter, Hiyori?
Dialogue: 5,0:17:50.95,0:17:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Please don't cry.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:56.21,0:18:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiyori had a high fever and was bedridden \Nuntil a few days later, when the marks disappeared.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:02.25,0:18:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the marks would reappear at the slightest exposure to sunlight,
Dialogue: 5,0:18:06.36,0:18:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,so we had to keep the shutters closed during the day.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:11.43,0:18:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Since then, Hiyori has rarely left the house
Dialogue: 5,0:18:15.76,0:18:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and has spent most of her life in the back room.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:20.97,0:18:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The lunar eclipse you and your wife saw
Dialogue: 5,0:18:23.02,0:18:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,must not have been a real lunar eclipse.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:26.93,0:18:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It was likely caused by a subspecies of Hihami \Nknown as Tsukihami, or "Moon Devourer" mushi.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:33.09,0:18:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,When an expectant mother is exposed to the light of a false lunar eclipse like that one,
Dialogue: 5,0:18:37.34,0:18:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,her unborn child is drained of color.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:39.89,0:18:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Once the child is born, exposure to \Nsunlight causes marks resembling a burn.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:45.69,0:18:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,In your case, one of your daughters \Nmust have avoided the eclipse's influence
Dialogue: 5,0:18:50.23,0:18:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,thanks to the other daughter{'s} shielding her from the light.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:57.95,0:19:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You protected me, Hiyori.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:02.59,0:19:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I will do my best to find a treatment for Hiyori{-san}.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:07.80,0:19:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,In return, would it be possible to ask \Nfor your help in ridding us of this eclipse?
Dialogue: 5,0:19:37.57,0:19:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,How come I'm the only one who can't go out?
Dialogue: 5,0:19:42.19,0:19:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Hinata's allowed to!
Dialogue: 5,0:19:45.08,0:19:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiyori, you're unwell.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:47.99,0:19:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're exposed to sunlight, you could die.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:51.08,0:19:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Look! All the things you like are right here.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:55.09,0:19:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want them!
Dialogue: 5,0:19:56.48,0:19:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanna go outside and play with Hinata!{so... go out at night??}
Dialogue: 5,0:20:04.19,0:20:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiyori?
Dialogue: 5,0:20:08.91,0:20:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at this!
Dialogue: 5,0:20:16.09,0:20:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, they're amazing!
Dialogue: 5,0:20:20.93,0:20:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,This is so nice.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:21.92,0:20:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,There are so many pretty things outside!
Dialogue: 5,0:20:24.61,0:20:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, I found a place with lots of {blooming }flowers.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:28.34,0:20:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a secret place that only I know of!
Dialogue: 5,0:20:31.25,0:20:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure it'll be fine if we \Ngo there on a day {that }the sun isn't out.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:34.81,0:20:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take you there sometime!
Dialogue: 5,0:20:37.99,0:20:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,'Kay!
Dialogue: 5,0:20:49.05,0:20:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so bright...
Dialogue: 5,0:20:53.31,0:20:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 5,0:20:55.27,0:20:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm okay.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:58.62,0:21:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiyori! Your face!{UV rays: the silent killer}
Dialogue: 5,0:21:04.82,0:21:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you not to take her outside!
Dialogue: 5,0:21:06.75,0:21:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you listen?
Dialogue: 5,0:21:10.17,0:21:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:11.95,0:21:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so sorry, Hiyori.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:16.31,0:21:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop telling her stories \Nthat make her want to go outside.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:21.23,0:21:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It will only make things harder for her.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:25.85,0:21:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:33.59,0:21:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,They're almost gone.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:35.40,0:21:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:37.41,0:21:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Hinata?
Dialogue: 5,0:21:39.91,0:21:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you pick me some flowers from that meadow?
Dialogue: 5,0:21:43.24,0:21:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 5,0:21:44.27,0:21:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, um...
Dialogue: 5,0:21:45.93,0:21:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry. I forgot where it was.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:51.33,0:21:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 5,0:21:58.87,0:22:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's put these on her next!
Dialogue: 5,0:22:00.40,0:22:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,'Kay!
Dialogue: 5,0:22:01.83,0:22:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Hinata{-chan}!
Dialogue: 5,0:22:04.84,0:22:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's play!
Dialogue: 5,0:22:08.09,0:22:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 5,0:22:09.36,0:22:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll come some other time.
Dialogue: 5,0:22:10.89,0:22:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 5,0:22:11.94,0:22:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's no fun without you!
Dialogue: 5,0:22:19.71,0:22:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry about that.
Dialogue: 5,0:22:22.15,0:22:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You can go, you know.
Dialogue: 5,0:22:24.19,0:22:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But I like being with you more, Hiyori.
Dialogue: 5,0:22:26.82,0:22:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Liar.
Dialogue: 5,0:22:28.17,0:22:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You {used to }love playing outside.
Dialogue: 5,0:22:31.01,0:22:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That's...
Dialogue: 5,0:22:32.87,0:22:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it because you feel guilty since \Nyou're the only one who can go out?
Dialogue: 5,0:22:37.51,0:22:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it because you feel sorry for me?
Dialogue: 5,0:22:40.65,0:22:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want your pity.
Dialogue: 5,0:22:45.89,0:22:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 5,0:22:47.14,0:22:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,what should I do, then?
Dialogue: 5,0:22:52.85,0:22:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Trade places...
Dialogue: 5,0:22:54.64,0:22:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Trade places with me!
Dialogue: 5,0:23:04.33,0:23:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that... even possible?
Dialogue: 5,0:23:09.45,0:23:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,If you can't,
Dialogue: 5,0:23:11.21,0:23:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,just go away already.
Dialogue: 5,0:23:16.41,0:23:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're next to me,
Dialogue: 5,0:23:18.84,0:23:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't help but think that I \Nshould've had a life like yours instead.
Dialogue: 5,0:23:30.92,0:23:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiyori? I'll leave your food {right }here, okay?
Dialogue: 5,0:23:48.91,0:23:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiyori...
Dialogue: 5,0:23:52.89,0:23:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd like to talk to you.
Dialogue: 5,0:23:58.59,0:24:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems your condition is caused by something similar to what's causing the current eclipse.
Dialogue: 5,0:24:05.73,0:24:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But you don't know how to fix it, right?
Dialogue: 5,0:24:09.22,0:24:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard you two talking earlier.
Dialogue: 5,0:24:11.95,0:24:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 5,0:24:13.59,0:24:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But if we can fix the eclipse,
Dialogue: 5,0:24:15.88,0:24:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,we might also find a way to make you better.
Dialogue: 5,0:24:21.05,0:24:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Hinata and I will go and help Ginko{-san}{ here} search.
Dialogue: 5,0:24:25.31,0:24:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry to leave you here alone,
Dialogue: 5,0:24:26.72,0:24:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,but it'll only be for a little while.
Dialogue: 5,0:25:04.13,0:25:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder how long it's been \Nsince I've walked outside during the day.
Dialogue: 5,0:25:11.41,0:25:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,This feels great!
Dialogue: 5,0:25:14.21,0:25:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, what a pretty bird.
Dialogue: 5,0:25:17.85,0:25:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder what kind of bug this is.
Dialogue: 5,0:25:28.49,0:25:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone looks so gloomy \Njust 'cause they can't be in the sunlight.
Dialogue: 5,0:25:34.37,0:25:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,At least now they have some \Nsense of how I've felt all this time.{she's only saying "i bet they now have a sense of how it feels to be in my shoes (getas)"}
Dialogue: 5,0:25:38.11,0:25:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Serves them right.
Dialogue: 5,0:25:39.83,0:25:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope this eclipse never ends.
Dialogue: 5,0:25:48.71,0:25:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The meadow that Hinata \Ntold me about should be this way.
Dialogue: 5,0:26:01.69,0:26:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Back then, I think we got about this far.
Dialogue: 5,0:26:06.93,0:26:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Afterward, Hinata carried me all the way home on her back.
Dialogue: 5,0:26:11.41,0:26:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That must've been really hard \Non a mountain path like this one.
Dialogue: 5,0:26:19.30,0:26:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't find it.{we still don't know the name of the mushi we saw that day}{lel}
Dialogue: 5,0:26:44.03,0:26:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Here it is!{rip}
Dialogue: 5,0:26:46.63,0:26:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is where it was.
Dialogue: 5,0:26:52.31,0:26:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,They're so pretty.
Dialogue: 5,0:26:53.79,0:26:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder what these flowers are called.
Dialogue: 5,0:26:57.21,0:26:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,They're shining.
Dialogue: 5,0:27:05.27,0:27:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow!
Dialogue: 5,0:27:06.46,0:27:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just like Hinata said.
Dialogue: 5,0:27:16.01,0:27:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish we could've seen this together.
Dialogue: 5,0:27:29.28,0:27:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, get him to be quiet already!{i know this feel}
Dialogue: 5,0:27:31.40,0:27:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He's making me even more nervous.
Dialogue: 5,0:27:33.14,0:27:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He can't help that he's hungry!
Dialogue: 5,0:27:41.83,0:27:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You came outside again?
Dialogue: 5,0:27:45.09,0:27:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 5,0:27:46.91,0:27:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm fine.
Dialogue: 5,0:27:49.71,0:27:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,How did you get those{ flowers}?
Dialogue: 5,0:27:51.94,0:27:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,"How?"
Dialogue: 5,0:27:53.28,0:27:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I found them.
Dialogue: 5,0:27:54.62,0:27:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,There were so many{ of them blooming}. It was beautiful.
Dialogue: 5,0:27:58.01,0:28:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Those flowers don't usually bloom this time of year.
Dialogue: 5,0:28:00.20,0:28:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That could be where the Hihami's root is.
Dialogue: 5,0:28:06.33,0:28:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you tell me where you found them?
Dialogue: 5,0:28:09.63,0:28:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 5,0:28:12.45,0:28:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,If this eclipse is left unchecked,
Dialogue: 5,0:28:14.68,0:28:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the shadow will continue to grow.
Dialogue: 5,0:28:16.72,0:28:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The darkness will spread,
Dialogue: 5,0:28:18.91,0:28:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,bringing with it a barren land \Nhospitable only to the mushi.
Dialogue: 5,0:28:22.72,0:28:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,If we don't do something about it soon, there won't be anything we {\i1}can{\i0} do.
Dialogue: 5,0:28:26.16,0:28:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But I want things to stay this way!
Dialogue: 5,0:28:30.41,0:28:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You are human, just like everyone else.
Dialogue: 5,0:28:34.05,0:28:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to eat food.
Dialogue: 5,0:28:36.39,0:28:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You may not be able to tolerate direct sunlight.
Dialogue: 5,0:28:38.56,0:28:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You may hate the sun.
Dialogue: 5,0:28:40.36,0:28:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But you are able to live because of its light.
Dialogue: 5,0:28:44.01,0:28:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You are just like that mushi.
Dialogue: 5,0:28:48.71,0:28:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The Hihami can only come \Nto the surface during an eclipse.
Dialogue: 5,0:28:54.39,0:28:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, it must hide deep underground.
Dialogue: 5,0:29:00.59,0:29:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you suppose it comes to the surface?
Dialogue: 5,0:29:04.21,0:29:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,There are mushi that spend their entire lives in darkness and have no need of light.
Dialogue: 5,0:29:10.15,0:29:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The Hihami may come to the surface
Dialogue: 5,0:29:12.44,0:29:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,because it {\i1}needs{\i0} {the }sunlight.
Dialogue: 5,0:29:15.14,0:29:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps it cannot live if it \Nalways remains underground.
Dialogue: 5,0:29:21.85,0:29:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, its root disappears \Nif exposed to that same light.
Dialogue: 5,0:29:26.05,0:29:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why its core creates a shadow \Nof mushi to protect its root from the sun,
Dialogue: 5,0:29:29.77,0:29:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,even as the core itself basks in it.
Dialogue: 5,0:29:34.05,0:29:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the same, aren't you?
Dialogue: 5,0:29:37.27,0:29:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why you're happy even \Nin a world as dimly lit as this one.
Dialogue: 5,0:29:42.29,0:29:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 5,0:29:44.49,0:29:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,if you close yourself off just like \Nyou were closed off in that room,{CR: as long as you remain closed off, like that room you were in,}{not being open-minded / thinking this dimly-lit world is enough for her}{hmm... "if you shut the door on every other possibility... etc etc}
Dialogue: 5,0:29:50.37,0:29:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,even this faint light will {soon }become engulfed by darkness.
Dialogue: 5,0:30:04.71,0:30:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}One of your daughters
Dialogue: 5,0:30:08.70,0:30:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\q2}must have avoided the eclipse's influence \Nthanks to the other daughter{'s} shielding her from the light.
Dialogue: 5,0:30:13.95,0:30:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Trade places with me!
Dialogue: 5,0:30:16.45,0:30:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...just go away already.
Dialogue: 5,0:30:26.20,0:30:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I should never have been born, Hiyori.
Dialogue: 5,0:30:51.07,0:30:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiyori,
Dialogue: 5,0:30:52.78,0:30:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,have you seen Hinata?
Dialogue: 5,0:30:56.77,0:30:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,She's not back yet.
Dialogue: 5,0:30:58.71,0:30:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna go look for her.
Dialogue: 5,0:31:00.65,0:31:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope nothing happened to her in the mountains.
Dialogue: 5,0:31:02.75,0:31:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's hope she wasn't influenced by the eclipse.
Dialogue: 5,0:31:05.93,0:31:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Occasionally, people vanish during an eclipse.
Dialogue: 5,0:31:09.85,0:31:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They sometimes become invisible to everyone except those who can see mushi.
Dialogue: 5,0:31:14.33,0:31:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see them, can't you?
Dialogue: 5,0:31:19.63,0:31:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't ask me.
Dialogue: 5,0:31:20.92,0:31:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure she'll be back soon.
Dialogue: 5,0:31:25.39,0:31:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Hinata!
Dialogue: 5,0:31:27.53,0:31:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Please respond!
Dialogue: 5,0:31:29.93,0:31:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Hinata!
Dialogue: 5,0:31:39.77,0:31:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's already been three days.{time sure flies}
Dialogue: 5,0:31:43.29,0:31:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Hinata, where are you?
Dialogue: 5,0:31:57.47,0:32:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't really vanish, did you?
Dialogue: 5,0:32:04.75,0:32:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Where'd you go?
Dialogue: 5,0:32:09.43,0:32:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,When I told you to go away,
Dialogue: 5,0:32:11.43,0:32:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't really mean it!
Dialogue: 5,0:32:16.25,0:32:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What are we gonna do?
Dialogue: 5,0:32:19.02,0:32:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It never even crossed my mind that the sun could vanish.
Dialogue: 5,0:32:24.05,0:32:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 5,0:32:26.09,0:32:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I took {it }for granted that it'd rise every day.
Dialogue: 5,0:32:33.25,0:32:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's right.
Dialogue: 5,0:32:34.52,0:32:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Because I thought Hinata would always stay by my side,
Dialogue: 5,0:32:38.52,0:32:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I said all those horrible things to her.
Dialogue: 5,0:32:41.15,0:32:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}To me,
Dialogue: 5,0:32:42.50,0:32:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Hinata was the sun.
Dialogue: 5,0:32:47.41,0:32:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And yet...{italics?}
Dialogue: 5,0:32:50.11,0:32:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 5,0:32:51.55,0:32:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm so sorry, Hinata.
Dialogue: 5,0:32:53.89,0:32:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Please come back!
Dialogue: 5,0:32:56.55,0:32:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Hinata, where are you?
Dialogue: 5,0:33:01.07,0:33:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Hinata!
Dialogue: 5,0:33:05.41,0:33:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I know!
Dialogue: 5,0:33:25.13,0:33:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Hinata!
Dialogue: 5,0:33:26.15,0:33:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hinata!
Dialogue: 5,0:33:27.87,0:33:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew you'd be here!
Dialogue: 5,0:33:31.67,0:33:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Hinata, what's wrong?
Dialogue: 5,0:33:37.47,0:33:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so sorry.
Dialogue: 5,0:33:39.32,0:33:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,This is all my fault, isn't it?
Dialogue: 5,0:33:42.03,0:33:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't say mean things like that anymore.
Dialogue: 5,0:33:46.71,0:33:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So please!
Dialogue: 5,0:33:50.19,0:33:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Please go back to being the cheerful, \Nkind sister you were when we were little!{what a selfish brat}
Dialogue: 5,0:34:00.99,0:34:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Ginko{-san}!
Dialogue: 5,0:34:02.64,0:34:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I found Hinata!
Dialogue: 5,0:34:08.13,0:34:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,She's already become invisible to the human eye.
Dialogue: 5,0:34:14.99,0:34:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Ginko{-san}, how can we get Hinata to go back to her old self?
Dialogue: 5,0:34:19.82,0:34:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,For starters, we need to end the Hihami eclipse.
Dialogue: 5,0:34:22.33,0:34:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That should scatter the mushi and lessen their influence.
Dialogue: 5,0:34:26.65,0:34:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The rest will depend on you{r} staying by her side \Nand talking to her as much as you can.
Dialogue: 5,0:34:52.25,0:34:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,This is it!
Dialogue: 5,0:34:53.36,0:34:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The root is probably under these flowers.
Dialogue: 5,0:34:55.44,0:34:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Please start digging right away!
Dialogue: 5,0:35:06.86,0:35:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I hit something.
Dialogue: 5,0:35:08.10,0:35:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Dig here!
Dialogue: 5,0:35:10.49,0:35:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What the heck {\i1}is{\i0} this?
Dialogue: 5,0:35:17.09,0:35:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it.
Dialogue: 5,0:35:18.46,0:35:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we just have to get it to a place where the sun's still shining.
Dialogue: 5,0:35:24.47,0:35:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Heave-ho!
Dialogue: 5,0:35:26.79,0:35:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Careful!
Dialogue: 5,0:35:34.07,0:35:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The sun's shining on that hill.
Dialogue: 5,0:35:36.53,0:35:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We've gotta take it over there.
Dialogue: 5,0:35:37.69,0:35:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it!
Dialogue: 5,0:35:50.43,0:35:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 5,0:35:51.62,0:35:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We're already past the hill!
Dialogue: 5,0:35:53.24,0:35:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How come we're still \Nunder that thing's shadow?
Dialogue: 5,0:35:57.25,0:35:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The shadow must be chasing us.
Dialogue: 5,0:36:00.57,0:36:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's try to pick up the pace!
Dialogue: 5,0:36:01.78,0:36:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 5,0:36:06.63,0:36:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder how the men are doing.
Dialogue: 5,0:36:09.02,0:36:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope they're okay.
Dialogue: 5,0:36:12.53,0:36:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Look!
Dialogue: 5,0:36:17.97,0:36:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, look!
Dialogue: 5,0:36:20.71,0:36:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The light!
Dialogue: 5,0:36:32.87,0:36:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiyori! The sun's back!
Dialogue: 5,0:36:37.31,0:36:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That's great!
Dialogue: 5,0:36:38.91,0:36:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 5,0:36:40.47,0:36:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We can get our lives back on track.
Dialogue: 5,0:36:46.17,0:36:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't feel bright anymore.
Dialogue: 5,0:36:49.09,0:36:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiyori?
Dialogue: 5,0:36:50.77,0:36:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you...
Dialogue: 5,0:36:54.81,0:36:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, what's happened to me?
Dialogue: 5,0:37:00.47,0:37:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though I'm in the sun,
Dialogue: 5,0:37:02.22,0:37:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm perfectly fine!{you have hinata to thank for it!!!}
Dialogue: 5,0:37:08.33,0:37:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a bit farther.
Dialogue: 5,0:37:09.72,0:37:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a little more till we're out of the shadow!
Dialogue: 5,0:37:24.31,0:37:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Sunlight!
Dialogue: 5,0:37:26.34,0:37:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Get the lid off!
Dialogue: 5,0:37:51.87,0:37:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It vanished.
Dialogue: 5,0:37:53.73,0:37:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, look at the sun.
Dialogue: 5,0:38:00.85,0:38:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The shadow's going away too.
Dialogue: 5,0:38:11.35,0:38:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Hooray! Hooray!
Dialogue: 5,0:38:12.67,0:38:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Phew...
Dialogue: 5,0:38:14.85,0:38:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We made it.
Dialogue: 5,0:38:20.53,0:38:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That's...
Dialogue: 5,0:38:28.79,0:38:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Ginko{-san}!
Dialogue: 5,0:38:32.81,0:38:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiyori?
Dialogue: 5,0:38:37.63,0:38:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 5,0:38:39.53,0:38:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The Hihami's light is typically comprised of wavelengths \Nthat have an ill effect on one's mind and body,
Dialogue: 5,0:38:44.88,0:38:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,but they seem to have beneficial effects on those affected by the Tsukihami.
Dialogue: 5,0:38:48.69,0:38:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That may explain it.
Dialogue: 5,0:38:52.31,0:38:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 5,0:38:54.73,0:38:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, I guess you no longer need this.
Dialogue: 5,0:38:59.89,0:39:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a shard of the Hihami's core.
Dialogue: 5,0:39:02.44,0:39:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's powerful and able to increase vitality.
Dialogue: 5,0:39:07.71,0:39:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought that it could help humans too.{the previous line is about vitality in general. plants, animals, everything. he moves on to how he thought it could positively affect humans too in the next line}
Dialogue: 5,0:39:12.89,0:39:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I give it to Hinata instead, then?
Dialogue: 5,0:39:17.83,0:39:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not?
Dialogue: 5,0:39:19.32,0:39:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't want it?
Dialogue: 5,0:39:24.37,0:39:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Given how responsive she is,
Dialogue: 5,0:39:27.22,0:39:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,it's only a matter of time \Nbefore she goes back to normal.
Dialogue: 5,0:39:30.61,0:39:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Just stay by her side until that happens.
Dialogue: 5,0:39:34.17,0:39:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, I understand.
Dialogue: 5,0:39:36.73,0:39:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's my turn to shine on Hinata.{;_;}
Dialogue: 5,0:39:43.25,0:39:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what should I do with this?
Dialogue: 5,0:39:55.37,0:39:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you're finally here, huh?
Dialogue: 5,0:39:58.57,0:40:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't seem like your wish came true.
Dialogue: 5,0:40:01.87,0:40:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It didn't!
Dialogue: 5,0:40:02.94,0:40:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't get to see a single mushi!
Dialogue: 5,0:40:04.88,0:40:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It began and ended just like any old eclipse, \Nand it was over in a flash!
Dialogue: 5,0:40:09.34,0:40:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing out of the ordinary happened!
Dialogue: 5,0:40:11.38,0:40:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That's good to hear.
Dialogue: 5,0:40:13.20,0:40:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's best when nothing unusual happens.
Dialogue: 5,0:40:16.85,0:40:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess you have a point there.
Dialogue: 5,0:40:18.89,0:40:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't {even }notice a slight increase in patients?
Dialogue: 5,0:40:21.55,0:40:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it...
Dialogue: 5,0:40:23.88,0:40:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,After the eclipse, some people were afraid of sunlight,
Dialogue: 5,0:40:27.60,0:40:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and others said they couldn't sleep{ at night}.{........................}
Dialogue: 5,0:40:30.19,0:40:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And? Are they better now?
Dialogue: 5,0:40:32.16,0:40:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I gave them medicine, \Nbut it hasn't had much of an effect.
Dialogue: 5,0:40:38.37,0:40:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't read my letter, did you?
Dialogue: 5,0:40:41.27,0:40:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Their symptoms are caused by mushi.
Dialogue: 5,0:40:43.52,0:40:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll get better once you \Ngive them the medicine I sent you.
Dialogue: 5,0:40:51.47,0:40:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You stay put and wait for me.
Dialogue: 5,0:40:52.90,0:40:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,When I get back, I wanna hear \Nwhat you were up to during the eclipse!
Dialogue: 5,0:40:55.64,0:40:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Nah, I've gotta get going.
Dialogue: 5,0:40:57.18,0:40:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 5,0:40:58.81,0:41:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,There's someone else I should tell that story to first.
Dialogue: 5,0:41:02.95,0:41:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You could at least tell me {\i1}some{\i0} of it. Just wait for me!
Dialogue: 5,0:41:06.15,0:41:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Some other day.
Dialogue: 5,0:41:17.05,0:41:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Tanyuu, you have a letter from Ginko.
Dialogue: 5,0:41:21.14,0:41:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The incident appears to have been safely resolved.
Dialogue: 5,0:41:24.07,0:41:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 5,0:41:26.39,0:41:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He plans to come here soon and tell you about it.
Dialogue: 5,0:41:29.84,0:41:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,He also has something he'd like to show you.
Dialogue: 5,0:41:35.29,0:41:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,"Soon," he said?
Dialogue: 5,0:41:38.09,0:41:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,His words are never very reliable.
Dialogue: 5,0:41:44.23,0:41:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 5,0:41:46.35,0:41:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I am patient.
Dialogue: 5,0:41:59.59,0:42:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like I slept a bit too long.
Dialogue: 5,0:42:12.50,0:42:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Up we go.{}
Dialogue: 5,0:42:17.35,0:42:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, what a fine day.
Dialogue: 5,0:42:27.71,0:42:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's hope nothing unusual happens today.
